<h3><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Fourier_transform&amp;action=edit&amp;section=28" title="Edit section: Two-dimensional functions">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Two-dimensional functions</span></h3>
<table class="wikitable">
<tr>
<th></th>
<th>Function</th>
<th>Fourier transform<br />
unitary, ordinary frequency</th>
<th>Fourier transform<br />
unitary, angular frequency</th>
<th>Fourier transform<br />
non-unitary, angular frequency</th>
<th>Remarks</th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td></td>
<td align="center"><span class="texhtml"><i>f</i>(<i>x</i>,<i>y</i>)</span></td>
<td align="center"><img class="tex" alt=" \hat{f}(\xi_x, \xi_y)=" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/math/4/5/1/451e3e24b723cef7a5c17321d7a2e14a.png" />
<p><img class="tex" alt="\iint f(x,y) e^{-2\pi i(\xi_x x+\xi_y y)}\,dxdy" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/math/c/6/2/c62c62000b0322ce0f50896b60ad3ce8.png" /></p>
</td>
<td align="center"><img class="tex" alt=" \hat{f}(\omega_x,\omega_y)=" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/math/3/0/0/3002217031f787eb6fe76ad73b1df5bc.png" />
<p><img class="tex" alt="\frac{1}{2 \pi} \iint f(x,y) e^{-i (\omega_x x +\omega_y y)}\, dxdy" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/math/a/9/a/a9a75d7b9bbd35df09337374d10af739.png" /></p>
</td>
<td align="center"><img class="tex" alt=" \hat{f}(\nu_x,\nu_y)=" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/math/c/2/3/c23fdd195c06d794b5cb34f53ad046ee.png" />
<p><img class="tex" alt="\iint f(x,y) e^{-i(\nu_x x+\nu_y y)}\, dxdy" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/math/8/0/a/80a3de45326ea65a0ce7be7333ea904e.png" /></p>
</td>
<td>The variables <i>ξ<sub>x</sub></i>, <i>ξ<sub>y</sub></i>, <i>ω<sub>x</sub></i>, <i>ω<sub>y</sub></i>, <i>ν<sub>x</sub></i> and <i>ν<sub>y</sub></i> are real numbers. The integrals are taken over the entire plane.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>401</td>
<td align="center"><img class="tex" alt="e^{-\pi\left(a^2x^2+b^2y^2\right)}" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/math/9/3/1/931f5518e05b470957d7377bb4ddac90.png" /></td>
<td align="center"><img class="tex" alt="\frac{1}{|ab|} e^{-\pi\left(\xi_x^2/a^2 + \xi_y^2/b^2\right)}" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/math/b/7/5/b7536db7374b5b1062552fd925fd25b2.png" /></td>
<td align="center"><img class="tex" alt="\frac{1}{2\pi\cdot|ab|} e^{\frac{-\left(\omega_x^2/a^2 + \omega_y^2/b^2\right)}{4\pi}}" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/math/0/0/0/00053ca405ca90e8409a65ab345a2a7a.png" /></td>
<td align="center"><img class="tex" alt="\frac{1}{|ab|} e^{\frac{-\left(\nu_x^2/a^2 + \nu_y^2/b^2\right)}{4\pi}}" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/math/0/a/6/0a6f247193c30d2ffb0342cf73255d4f.png" /></td>
<td>Both functions are Gaussians, which may not have unit volume.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>402</td>
<td><img class="tex" alt="\mathrm{circ}(\sqrt{x^2+y^2})" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/math/3/0/c/30c58ddb89eee3081ec3c30fb0c89e47.png" /></td>
<td align="center"><img class="tex" alt=" \frac{J_1\left(2 \pi \sqrt{\xi_x^2+\xi_y^2}\right)}{\sqrt{\xi_x^2+\xi_y^2}}" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/math/d/7/a/d7a773cf9b01c3dd6c01bcf6eb115ab5.png" /></td>
<td align="center"><img class="tex" alt=" \frac{J_1\left(\sqrt{\omega_x^2+\omega_y^2}\right)}{\sqrt{\omega_x^2+\omega_y^2}}" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/math/0/5/0/050529771b19f00741fa801436536a94.png" /></td>
<td align="center"><img class="tex" alt=" \frac{2\pi J_1\left(\sqrt{\nu_x^2+\nu_y^2}\right)}{\sqrt{\nu_x^2+\nu_y^2}}" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/math/d/a/7/da7f27c750f6db98891eca88b1200153.png" /></td>
<td>The function is defined by circ(<i>r</i>)=1 0≤<i>r</i>≤1, and is 0 otherwise. This is the Airy distribution and is expressed using J<sub>1</sub> (the order 1 Bessel function of the first kind). <cite class="inline">(<a href="#CITEREFSteinWeiss1971" title="">Stein &amp; Weiss 1971</a>, Thm. IV.3.3)</cite></td>
</tr>
</table>
<p><a name="Formulas_for_general_n-dimensional_functions" id="Formulas_for_general_n-dimensional_functions"></a></p>
<h3><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Fourier_transform&amp;action=edit&amp;section=29" title="Edit section: Formulas for general n-dimensional functions">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Formulas for general <i>n</i>-dimensional functions</span></h3>
<table class="wikitable">
<tr>
<th></th>
<th>Function</th>
<th>Fourier transform<br />
unitary, ordinary frequency</th>
<th>Fourier transform<br />
unitary, angular frequency</th>
<th>Fourier transform<br />
non-unitary, angular frequency</th>
<th>Remarks</th>
