<tr>
<td>501</td>
<td><span class="texhtml">χ<sub>[0,1]</sub>( | <i>x</i> | )(1 − | <i>x</i> | <sup>2</sup>)<sup>δ</sup></span></td>
<td align="center"><span class="texhtml">π <sup>− δ</sup>Γ(δ + 1) | ξ | <sup>− (<i>n</i> / 2) − δ</sup></span><br />
<img class="tex" alt="\cdot J_{n/2+\delta}(2\pi|\xi|)" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/math/5/8/1/5811cf5297ed583a1eaf58532bf20c29.png" /></td>
<td align="center"><img class="tex" alt=" 2^{-\delta}\Gamma(\delta+1)\left|\omega\right|^{-(n/2)-\delta}" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/math/f/4/0/f4072caac2944528df57efb0eff34d2a.png" /><br />
<img class="tex" alt="\cdot J_{n/2+\delta}(|\omega|)" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/math/6/9/d/69d04197bfd2228667508ce8c314348f.png" /></td>
<td align="center"><img class="tex" alt=" \pi^{-\delta}\Gamma(\delta+1)\left|\frac{\nu}{2\pi}\right|^{-(n/2)-\delta}" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/math/d/0/f/d0fdb5dc5c42107d361d3071cdcf2fd2.png" /><br />
<img class="tex" alt="\cdot J_{n/2+\delta}(|\nu|)" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/math/a/d/e/ade2d0d803414a86bca822446fa6f521.png" /></td>
<td>The function χ<sub>[0,1]</sub> is the <a href="/wiki/Indicator_function" title="Indicator function">characteristic function</a> of the interval [0,1]. The function <i>Γ</i>(<i>x</i>) is the gamma function. The function <i>J</i><sub><i>n</i>/2&#160;+&#160;<i>δ</i></sub> a Bessel function of the first kind with order <i>n/2+δ</i>. Taking <i>n</i>&#160;=&#160;2 and <i>δ</i>&#160;=&#160;0 produces 402. <cite class="inline">(<a href="#CITEREFSteinWeiss1971" title="">Stein &amp; Weiss 1971</a>, Thm. 4.13)</cite></td>
</tr>
</table>
